Entries.default: "It was their first hanging. Had the rope too long so it cut the tosser's head right off."
"Been slower than two slugs swiving, since Aeldys put the lid on it."
"Winds'll be changing soon enough. Benweth can't resist throwing another bash for long."
"Best hope you don't roll another pair, eh?"
"Aw. Looks like it just ain't your day."
"Going to lose more than your shirt, I wager."
"There he blows! Spewing chunks like chumming the waters. Boom!"
"I'll drink from two cups at once, betcha!"
"Ha! Benweth put 'em to work on the forge."
"Wish I could've seen that Dyrwoodan's face."
"It is. I'm telling you, I saw it."
